    <title>Chern classes of logarithmic derivations for some non-free arrangements</title>
    <summary>  Paolo Aluffi showed that the Chern--Schwartz--MacPherson class of the
complement of a free arrangement agrees with the total Chern class of the sheaf
of logarithmic derivations along the arrangement. We describe the defect of
equality of the two classes for locally tame arrangements with isolated
non-free singular loci.
</summary>
